{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcwLu83F1ZpTkz6bZfrfb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Nice — stale Docker layer caching on the lockfile is a classic one, and easy to lose hours to since the build \"succeeds\" with old deps. Let me save that as a lesson so a future session doesn't re-debug it."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5595,"cache_read_input_tokens":16984,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5595},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"433fd3c5-2c13-44af-85b1-4b7202831812","uuid":"2d88b0c1-3b32-423f-b032-bd3798de0b35","request_id":"req_011CcwLu6kbvdJa9pE2GGvep"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcwLu83F1ZpTkz6bZfrfb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0149V3twXq8BywzXX5RdE4nK","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/davidlayson/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-claude-501--Users-davidlayson-83ee2e2e-2641-4713-b439-5260ae8e5d1e-scratchpad/memory/lesson-docker-stale-lockfile-cache.md","content":"---\nname: lesson-docker-stale-lockfile-cache\ndescription: Deploy failing on stale deps — suspect a cached Dockerfile lockfile layer; clear the build cache\nmetadata:\n  type: feedback\n---\n\nA deploy kept failing because the Dockerfile was caching a stale lockfile — the build \"succeeded\" but ran against old dependencies. Clearing the build cache fixed it.\n\n**Why:** Docker layer caching keeps an old lockfile-copy/install layer even after the lockfile changes upstream, so the image installs stale deps while the build reports success — the failure surfaces later at runtime/deploy, far from the cause.\n\n**How to apply:** When a deploy fails on dependency/version mismatches that \"shouldn't\" be wrong given the current lockfile, suspect the Docker build cache before re-checking the deps themselves. Clear the build cache (or bust the relevant layer) and rebuild. Related to [[lesson-staging-debug-swallows-errors]] — both are cases where the real error hides behind a layer that looks fine.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5595,"cache_read_input_tokens":16984,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5595},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"433fd3c5-2c13-44af-85b1-4b7202831812","uuid":"0a41e2e0-d659-4715-9a8d-a7ae5d61fc0b","request_id":"req_011CcwLu6kbvdJa9pE2GGvep"}
